news_header: 157 killer whales stranded in Tasmania; rescuing them is challenging due to their weight and location.
news_original_title: Why do whales and dolphins strand?
news_text: 157 killer whales have stranded on a remote beach in Tasmania. Most are alive, but rescuing them is difficult due to their weight and location. Mass strandings often occur due to navigational errors, social behavior, and human-made noise. The article discusses the challenges and causes of whale strandings.
